<!-- Backend Setup -->

<!-- Dependencies -->

npm i express cors dotenv mongodb mongoose

express will handle our API request from the font end

cors is a security thing, basically helps us to configure the backend to accpet our block request that come from different domains & ports.

dotenv to set enviroment variables

mongodb mongoose will help us interact with our data base from our backend code

<!-- Dev Dependencies -->

npm i ts-node typescript nodemon @types/express @types/cors @types/node --save-dev

ts-node is basicllay typescript for node

typscript it will install typescript interactual in the project

nodemon is for hard reloading it means server is going to restart automatically and give us the changes.

@types will helps us like intelisense

<!-- Then install typescript config  -->

npx tsc --init
